## What's included

The full monorepo with all packages renamed from `@amplitude/*` → `@acai/*`:

| Package | Renamed to |
|---|---|
| `@amplitude/node` | `acai-node` |
| `@amplitude/types` | `@acai/types` |
| `@amplitude/identify` | `@acai/identify` |
| `@amplitude/identity` | `@acai/identity` |
| `@amplitude/utils` | `@acai/utils` |

All internal SDK references, logger prefixes, global namespaces, class names, and comments have been updated to `acai`. The server URL is set to a placeholder — see step 1 below.

---

## Deployment Steps

### 1. Set your server URL
Open `packages/node/src/constants.ts` and replace:
```typescript
export const ACAI_SERVER_URL = 'https://YOUR_SERVER_URL_HERE/2/httpapi';
```

### 2. Push to GitHub
```bash
cd acai-node
git remote add origin https://github.com/your-org/acai-node.git
git push -u origin main
```

### 3. Build & test locally
```bash
yarn install
yarn build
yarn test
```

### 4. Publish to npm (when ready)
Create an npm account/org, get an `NPM_TOKEN`, then:
```bash
# Add secret to GitHub: Settings → Secrets → NPM_TOKEN
# Then tag a release to trigger auto-publish:
git tag v1.0.0
git push origin v1.0.0
```
The included `.github/workflows/publish.yml` will automatically publish all packages to npm in the correct dependency order when you push a `v*` tag.

### 5. Users install it as:
```bash
npm install acai-node
```
```typescript
import { init } from 'acai-node';
const client = init('YOUR_API_KEY');
```
